        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 27 at 10:00PM MDT until June 27 at 11:00PM MDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>SVRGLD

The National Weather Service in Goodland has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Western Thomas County in northwestern Kansas...
Sherman County in northwestern Kansas...

* Until 1100 PM MDT/midnight CDT/.

* At 959 PM MDT/1059 PM CDT/, a severe thunderstorm was located 4
miles east of Goodland, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Brewster.

This includes Interstate 70 in Kansas between mile markers 11 and 46.

The National Weather Service in Goodland measured a 59 mph wind gust
and half inch hail at 948 pm MDT.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall with this storm may lead to localized flooding.
Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
